items.name: Batman Adventures Style LoRA
items.description:
Batman Adventures style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon üÖøÔ∏è or feel free to buy me a coffee ‚òï


Someone kindly asked me to make this style LoRA and it reminded me of my childhood. Use it with AnyLoRA ckpt at weight 1. The trigger batman adventures should increase the accuracy.

I suggest "None" as the upscaler for highres fix, to avoid cleaning the image and losing the grainy effect.

As someone asked me to do this and it's kind of hard to use to get good stuff, I'm locking the comment section and the reviews.


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Serval Landau (Honkai Star Rail)
items.description:
Created by GeomanticArts

This one took a lot of work. This is the 11th training of this particular character. There's just no art of her and training entirely on screenshots gives 1 very fixed outfit and an in-game appearance. Well, that's not what I'm looking for in a LoRA. It should be flexible and allow you to change appearances easily.
More or less this accomplishes that. It is -possible- to change outfits here. But it's quite tricky. The clothing is still very 'sticky' to the character and does not change easily. Turning the clothing items to high weights helps, but there are still some pieces of apparel that just don't change no matter what. Anything dress-like will look more like the normal outfit. Definitely not the highest quality LoRA I have uploaded here, but it's a character with very, very little art so it was an interesting challenge nonetheless.

Example images all made with AOM2-7thV3_C_40 at weight 1

'Serval Landau [Honkai Star Rail]' - Example prompt for the normal outfit. (sleeveless:1.2) recommended for basically all other appearances unless you want sleeves.

v15 update - Here's another shot. I nuked the entire dataset. Purged all the tags. Started again. Took some different screenshots. I think this one is better. Still has sticky clothing, but I found it more adjustable than previous attempts. The difficulty is really getting the clothes to change, not to generate the default outfit. Don't specify clothing in particular and you'll get the normal outfit.

LoRA metadata has all the tags used.

The trainer's twitter can be found at https://twitter.com/GeomanticArts

Trained on NAI.

items.name: That one TF2 map you played on a community server a while back
items.description:
Real gamers remember cp_thrembo

This lora intends to create screenshots of empty TF2 maps.

It's an update of my old TF2 maps checkpoint but since i can't update that page with a lora i'm posting it seperately here:

  • File is an actual lora this time

  • expanded the dataset to about 400 high-quality images, the new ones are all preview images from all-time most popular workshop maps

  • ran them all through an autotagger and then added some tf2-specific tags manually

  • tf2 specific tags include: gamemode (ctf,cp,5cp,payload,...), environment style (spytech, badlands, industrial, ...), team color (blu/red) and others (halloween, official,...)

  • Trained on nai, this also means you should prompt it booru-style and it might be compatible with anime/meme loras?

Doesn't work as well as i would have wanted but it's still worth uploading. Might work better if i prune the tags, since it acts a bit strangely about those. I recommend starting with a prompt from one of my new example images and adjusting from there.

The QBZ-191 is the newest Chinese assault rifle that was designed by Norinco. Revealed on the 70th Anniversary National Day military parade on October 1, 2019, the 191 aims to replace the QBZ-95 and rectify the various issues that arose from the 95 platform, such as ergonomics.

Designed to be a conventional configuration compared to the 95, it features improved ergonomics, ambidextrous usability, and better reliability across various environments. It comes with a full-length Picatinny rail on the top and has backup iron sights that can be folded down if needed. Most of the firearm is made out of aluminum alloys while the stock, grip, and stock are made of a polymer. The handguard can be fitted with additional attachment rails for various accessories.

The rifle sports a four-position adjustable stock, an ambidextrous fire selector, and lengthened magazine release lever that's installed in front of the trigger guard for ease of use when wearing gloves. The magazine was redesigned to have a better grip alongside having a transparent ammunition checking window.

The rifle uses the 5.8x42mm caliber, the Chinese equivalent to the 5.56x45mm NATO, with a redesigned DBP-191 ammunition to have better ballistic performance in medium to long ranges.

items.name: Sailor Moon Outfit LoRA
items.description:
Sailor Moon Outfit LoRA

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

V2

This model was trained using 91 images of different characters wearing a sailor moon cosplay. It was trained on the NAI model so it should work with most anime models.

Triggerword is sailor moon outfit

Recommended weight is 0.8 to 1.

Examples were generated on JavaMix with 20 steps on euler a, hires fix by 1.5 on 0.4 denoising and adetailer for the faces (face_yolov8n)

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

V1

This model was trained using 136 images of characters from the show Sailor Moon wearing their signature outfits, and some cosplays. It was trained on the NAI model so it should work with most anime based models.

The model is quite strong so I recommend to not go above 0.6 weight, or the rest of the image might look weird. It was specifically trained on the outfit, and not the faces or poses, so make sure to describe those in your prompt to not get weird faces. It is not perfect so it might require some inpainting.

Trigger word is sailor outfit, if you want the signature gloves add elbow gloves. Should work with other character LoRA's. You can also add any color in front of the tag to give the outfit a fixed color.

Example images were generated using AOM2 hard with 30-50 steps.

items.name: Akatsuki Souken (hentai model)
items.description:
I used a dataset of around ~315 images for v2 and I used Source checkpoint: AnyHentai as the base model (the 2.0 one, was +7GB). Lora here.

„ÅÇ„Å™„Åü„Åå„Åù„ÅÆËëóËÄÖ„Åß„ÅÇ„Çä„ÄÅ„Åì„Çå„ÇíË™≠„Çì„Åß„ÅÑ„Çã„Å™„Çâ„ÄÅ„Åì„ÅÆ„É¢„Éá„É´„Çí‰Ωø„Å£„Å¶„Ç≥„É≥„ÉÜ„É≥„ÉÑ„Çí‰ªä„Åæ„Åß„Çà„Çä„ÇÇÈÄü„Åè‰ΩúÊàê„Åó„ÄÅ„Çà„ÇäÂ§ö„Åè„ÅÆ„Ç≥„É≥„ÉÜ„É≥„ÉÑ„ÇíÂÖ¨Èñã„Åó„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑ„ÄÇ‰∏çÊ≠£Á¢∫„Å™ÈÉ®ÂàÜ„ÇíÊèè„ÅçÁõ¥„Åô„Åã„ÄÅ„Åù„Çå„Çâ„Çí„Ç¢„Ç§„Éá„Ç¢„ÇíÂæó„Çã„Åü„ÇÅ„Å´‰Ωø„Å£„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑ„ÄÇ

PS: This is just a NSFW model made after Akatsuki Souken circle to output images with similar style and body type that the mangas have. I made this model to share author's name to more people that might be interested in it, and hoping the author finds the model in the future and uses it to get ideas, or use it in his own work to produce more content.

Settings:

  • Sampler: Euler a / DMP++ SDE Karras it's what I use

  • Size: 512-512 (didn't test for other resolutions)

  • Clip skip: 2 (I used clip skip 2 mostly for image generation, but initially I was using clip skip 1 and seems fine)

  • Sampling Steps: 20-30 (I use mainly 30, but the coherency drops down at 20 for certain complex prompts, test for yourself, sometimes I go 28-35 if I find a seed I like the output)

  • Hiresfix upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x Anime6B on 2x, steps: 20, denoise 0.5 (I didn't test higher or lower than 0.5).

  • Cfg scale: 6 (6-11 I use)


Prompts about the x-ray/manga panels:

  • (manga panels) - produce cutouts in the image and usually if there is genitalia in the image will zoom on it

  • (x-ray) / (xray) - produce cutouts in the image and if there is intercourse will show the classic x-ray of akatsuki souken

  • (manga panels), (x-ray) - produce (sometimes) a mix of both

  • sex - produce blowjob mainly as a standalone word (by adding ,mating, thrusting, couple, you get sex, tends to produce sexual NSFW content)


Negative prompt: easynegative, badhandv4, lr, beard, curly, veiny, muscular, ((bodybuilder)), facial hair, mustache, lowres, fewer fingers, out of frame, jpeg artifacts, ugly, duplicate, morbid,mutilated, extra fingers, mutated hands, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn face, mutation, deformed, blurry, dehydrated, bad anatomy, bad proportions, extra limbs, cloned face, disfigured, gross proportions, malformed limbs, missing arms, missing legs, extra arms, extra legs, fused fingers,

I used that one for all images but you can change/edit, and make it better. Easynegative and badhandv4 are textual inversions (embeddings).

How I create prompts:
- I go in chatgpt, I give it one or three examples of prompts that I already have and I tell it:
"I am generating images for an Image generator text, the text it needs is special and the template for it is: (word,word,word),(word,word,word),...,(word,word,word), (details:1.3),(masterpiece:1.3).
- The reason I use (word,word,word) is so I box things together and be able to change easier, (green eyes,makeup,glasses),(pendulous breasts,erect nipple,pasties).
- Then chatgpt just generate for me easy prompts, I use same negative prompt

What's new in v2:
- The training, I carefully edited in photoshop around +200 images (probably 250). I did edit and made sure that there are no smearing like the images in V1. Most images should end up more crisp. The amount of smearing should be 3-5% max, so not noticeable my opinion (compared to what it used to be). Total img used around ~315(60-70 for v1 as comparison).

- The nipples look better. In v1 a lot of nipples had double nipple or it was so erect it launched itself out of the body.

- The color and style changes. I used around half of his works that he ever published (I think, if not 50% then 25% for sure). Because there are volumes from years ago and more recent ones, the "style" he used to draw changed so this will be seen in the final result. It won't feel probably like Akatsuki souken the final output, but more like a "high quality" one. Which might be good or bad, depends on ur taste. I didn't try combining v1 and v2 (maybe that could make the style more like v1 if that's ur taste).
- Downgrades: 1)
Because the volume of images is higher, the amount of "internal shots" that I put are so many, and look different so it's not as crispy as v1. V1 had only a few images, so now I'd say when a good result occur, it's usually better than v1, but v2 is inaccurate, so most x-ray might be bad.

2) Also the "sex" prompt produces a blowjob scene instead of a sex scene. I think it's because there were too many blowjob scenes I added in there. So the conclusion is it's hard to obtain NSFW stuff. I would probably use "lora" or control net to obtain certain things that used to be easier in v1. I think combining v1 with v2 or v2 with some other heavy hentai model might solve this issue.

My advice if you want something weird or whatever are your needs is combine models.
1) Comparison Image for v2 combined with a custom model I have.
2) Comparison Image for v2 combined with same custom model I have

For 2nd I think I used "huge pendulous saggy breasts" or something and it got that crazy result XD. Either way I think the =.= way to go is combining models.

„ÅÇ„Å™„Åü„Åå„Åù„ÅÆËëóËÄÖ„Åß„ÅÇ„Çä„ÄÅ„Åì„Çå„ÇíË™≠„Çì„Åß„ÅÑ„Çã„Å™„Çâ„ÄÅ„Åì„ÅÆ„É¢„Éá„É´„Çí‰Ωø„Å£„Å¶„Ç≥„É≥„ÉÜ„É≥„ÉÑ„Çí‰ªä„Åæ„Åß„Çà„Çä„ÇÇÈÄü„Åè‰ΩúÊàê„Åó„ÄÅ„Çà„ÇäÂ§ö„Åè„ÅÆ„Ç≥„É≥„ÉÜ„É≥„ÉÑ„ÇíÂÖ¨Èñã„Åó„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑ„ÄÇ‰∏çÊ≠£Á¢∫„Å™ÈÉ®ÂàÜ„ÇíÊèè„ÅçÁõ¥„Åô„Åã„ÄÅ„Åù„Çå„Çâ„Çí„Ç¢„Ç§„Éá„Ç¢„ÇíÂæó„Çã„Åü„ÇÅ„Å´‰Ωø„Å£„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑ„ÄÇ

TL;DR It's a hentai model trained on images from a Circle called Akatsuki Souken , it should output images with that style in mind

Q: Why did you do it?
A: I did this model so others can enjoy more content and find out more about the author. But personally I hope the author finds the model and use it himself to produce more content, he would only need to redraw certain parts, and make way more content than before

Settings:

  • Sampler: Euler a / DMP++ SDE Karras it's what I used, but you can test yourself (others samplers give interesting results as well)

  • Size: 512-512 works the best, ocasionally I tested with 512-768 and I get mix results.

  • Clip skip: 2 (It seems to improve everything, and reduce the cutouts panels that appear in images and improve eye/face/easier to get a background)

  • Sampling Steps: 20-30 (I also tested with 150, but my first 60% tests I used 20 without realizing then I switched to 30 mainly)

  • Hiresfix upscaler: 4x-UltraSharp on 2x, steps: 20, denoise 0.5 (0.2-0.5) seems ok results (took it from Olivio Sarikas) . Latent and R-ESRGAN 4x Anime6B also similar results

  • Cfg scale: 6 (6-11 I used. I noticed the higher I go the worse results I get)


Prompts about the x-ray/manga panels:

  • (manga panels) - produce cutouts in the image and usually if there is genitalia in the image will zoom on it

  • (x-ray) / (xray) - produce cutouts in the image and if there is intercourse will show the classic x-ray of akatsuki souken, kinda distorted since the dataset was small

  • (manga panels), (x-ray) - produce (sometimes) a mix of both

  • sex - produce intercourse (usually no cutouts)


Negative prompt: easynegative, badhandv4, lr, beard, curly, veiny, muscular, ((bodybuilder)), facial hair, mustache, lowres, fewer fingers, out of frame, jpeg artifacts, ugly, duplicate, morbid,mutilated, extra fingers, mutated hands, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn face, mutation, deformed, blurry, dehydrated, bad anatomy, bad proportions, extra limbs, cloned face, disfigured, gross proportions, malformed limbs, missing arms, missing legs, extra arms, extra legs, fused fingers,

I used that one for all images but you can change/edit, and make it better. Easynegative and badhandv4 are textual inversions (embeddings).

DataSet
I trained with 4 concepts the prompts I used(if I remember correctly) for those are
- akatsuki souken plump girl (around 20 img) [images with girls]
- akatsuki souken plump girl sex (around 21 img) [images with girls that make sex or blowjob and no manga panel in the image]
- akatsuki souken plump girl x-ray (around 16 img) [all images contain a girl that make sex and have internal view with the womb as manga panels]
- akatsuki souken plump girl manga panels (around 6 img) [the images contain image with the girl and 1-2 manga panel in the image that showcase either her boobs or anus or zoomed in on vag

Images training dataset
The images I used to train are RAW textless versions that I did edit out bits and cutouts in photoshop. I am a noob at editing photos so there are a lot of artifacts in the original images I did train. Sometimes u might see it yourself if certain "cutouts" or "backgrounds" look funky in the generations. I originally planned to add way more than 70 images (+1000), but it take so long to edit images that I don't think I will do that too soon. All images I resized them to 512x512 . I trained a model without modifying the manga panels but you would get weird results such as "male heads" and manga cutouts in scenes that you usually don't want which makes results unusable. So editing in photoshop is a necessity for most images (that's why only 70 img)

Machine used to train
I used runpod stable difussion 5:0 template and A6000 to train it and test (I have 2019 macOS can't train on my laptop sadly)

How easy is to use it: 5/10. Personally I am a noob and takes me a while to get the image I have in mind, Overall I was able to get almost anything I wanted from him that I like tweaking settings.

TIP:
I actually noticed that I have a hard time getting "crisp" results by myself, to fix that I went to chatGPT (3.5) and I asked him for 10 ideas such as:
"A surfer chick wearing a colorful wetsuit, riding the waves at a beautiful beach in Hawaii."
Then I learned chatGPT to spit out a version like this:
"The surfer chick rides the waves at a beautiful beach in Hawaii, dressed in a (vibrant) wetsuit that catches the eye with its (colorful) design. The (form-fitting) suit hugs her (athletic) figure, allowing for freedom of movement as she gracefully navigates the waves. Her (long) hair is tied back in a (messy) bun, with a (sun-kissed) complexion that adds to her (beachy) vibe. The (cool) water sprays her face as she rides the waves with (skill) and (determination), navigating the (challenging) surf with ease. The (sleek) surfboard is an extension of her body, as she deftly maneuvers it with (precision) and (grace). The (scenic) beauty of the beach and the (salty) air adds to the (thrill) of the ride, making for an (unforgettable) experience. Despite the (dangerous) nature of the sport, the surfer chick exudes (fearlessness) and (adventure), fully embracing the thrill of the ride."

I called writing in that style "akatsuki style", then I would give any sentence to chatGPT and tell it to write in akatsuki style and would output a version of text like that. By doing like this I could get quite good results (non nsfw). Then all u have to do is copy that text into the a1111 as prompt (or in chatGPT and get yourself ur own style, works with other models as well this chatGPT idea)

PS: Try adding --no-half-vae in command args, runpod dreambooth is tricky to setup, and my model sometimes fail to make an image, I noticed "--no-half-vae" reduced the amount of failures significantly, with this only 1 image out of 20 fails and give an error, there is a way to disable the checkup (which should stop the errors all together, but I didn't managed yet to do that)

items.name: Atey Ghailan style
items.description:
Atey Ghailan, also known as "Snatti," is an Iraqi-Swedish concept artist and illustrator. He is recognized for his intricate and detailed artwork, often featuring fantastical characters and imaginative worlds.

Ghailan's illustrations showcase a fusion of cultural influences, blending Middle Eastern aesthetics with elements of fantasy, science fiction, and mythology. His artwork is characterized by the meticulous attention to detail, vibrant color palettes, and the use of ornate patterns and textures.

One of his notable series is "Secret Friends," where he creates whimsical and enchanting portraits of imaginary creatures, each with their own unique personality and story. These illustrations capture a sense of wonder and invite viewers into a world of imagination and exploration.

Ghailan's artistry extends beyond his imaginative character designs. He is skilled at creating immersive environments and landscapes, using his illustrations to transport viewers to otherworldly settings filled with intricate architecture and lush natural elements.

His digital painting techniques allow for the incorporation of intricate details and lighting effects, enhancing the depth and realism of his artwork. Ghailan's ability to create emotionally resonant characters and narratives adds depth and storytelling to his illustrations, drawing viewers into his fantastical realms.

Atey Ghailan's artwork has gained recognition and has been featured in galleries, books, and exhibitions. His distinct style and ability to blend cultural influences with elements of fantasy and mythology make him a noteworthy artist in the realm of concept art and illustration. His illustrations invite viewers to immerse themselves in richly detailed worlds, evoking a sense of awe and curiosity.

items.name: Product Design (Elegant minimalism-eddiemauro) LORA
items.description:
Before to use

  • You have to know how works Stable Diffusion. I recommend using Automatic1111 like an interface to launch the model.

  • This is a model trained on SD 1.5 model, so you have to consider that it is not perfect. I have to make so much testing before to arrive to a stable generation. I will enhance the model when a better base model arrives (like SD XL new one).

  • This is a LORA model, so it is recommended to use like an extension of a Checkpoint. I recommend you to use realistic dataset models.

  • I recommend you to follow me on my instagram account, where I will explain about AI image generation: https://www.instagram.com/eddiemauro.design/

Intro

PRODUCT DESIGN (Elegant minimalism-eddiemauro) LORA: Hi, I‚Äôm a product and car designer, and I‚Äôm so excited to test with AI, I think is a good tool for designing. This tool (Lora) is so useful for the design process (shapes-ideas generation), but more than that it helps so much to refine aesthetically. Also, you can turn sketch and 3D schemes into render style. I created a basic Lora and tested it with so many kinds of checkpoints, and the result was a different type of "minimalism". The style is more aggressive and elegant (taken from Szechuan), but it preserves the minimalism style. Furthermore, the colors tend to be darker and opaque.

If you want to support my work and help me to upload more models (with better quality), you can do it by entering here and donating, I would greatly appreciate it: https://ko-fi.com/eddiemauro

Installation

  • I use Automatic1111, the best UI for Stable Diffusion image generation, so I recommend you to install locally or use it online with some Colab or other hosting. You can find online instructions or videos to do that. If you are going to install locally, you can watch this tutorial online and I recommend you to have at least a 6-8 Gb of VRAM Graphic Card (nvidia) to have a stable interface and launch with ‚ÄúMicrosoft Edge‚Äù because you will have problems on ‚ÄúGoogle Chrome‚Äù. Try also to install ‚Äúmedvram‚Äù or ‚Äúlowvram‚Äù options besides ‚Äúxformers‚Äù (search online how to).

  • This is a Lora model. You can watch this video to know how to install it. It is just to download a file and put it inside Lora file models. The Lora file extension is ‚Äú.safetensor‚Äù, and mostly the size is lower than a Checkpoint (that could be more than a gigabit).

  • You have to install also a Checkpoint model to use with, select one focused on realism visualization or 3D/render aspect.

  • Please for image creation you have to follow all my recommendations, if you don't, it is impossible to generate a good image quality. Also, you have to consider that from today AI image generation is not so consistent and perfect, you have to invest time to get it and make plenty of tests.

Recommendations for image generation

  • Checkpoint best models: ¬†SD 1.5 based models. It is mandatory to use with a checkpoint called "Szechuan Special Sauce RC003" or "Experience v8", so download first, install and load inside SD UI.¬†

  • Activation token/caption: Inside prompt space, the first word has to be: ‚Äúemauromin‚Äùor ‚Äúemauromin style‚Äù to activate the style. It is mandatory, if you don't do it, it will not work properly.

  • Another recommended prompting: Inside prompt you can use those words that will enhance the image generation: in the positive space, ‚Äúfuturistic, finely detailed, purism, ue 5, a computer rendering, minimalism, octane render, 4k‚Äù; in the negative space: ‚Äú(worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale)), cropped, text, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, duplicate, blurry, semi-realistic, out of frame, ugly, deformed‚Äù. You can also watch the image metadata of example images here and simulate the prompt.

  • Textual inversion/embedding or Lora tool recommended: I consider that ‚ÄúEasyNegative‚Äù is one best of textual inversion for negative prompt space, you should use it. Download here and install it, putting the file inside ‚Äúembeddings‚Äù. You can use it also ‚ÄúDetail Tweaker‚Äù to even reduce the details of the image, for that, you have to download from here, install like a Lora and use it inside positive prompt with a value of ‚Äú-0.5‚Äù. Use it when you realize the checkpoint used has so many details, but not when you see that minimalism is on it. This can change the shape of objects considerably.

  • Lora's weight: I'm trying to enhance the model, for now, this model works fine from 0.7 to 1, the most you increase the value, minimalism is higher. Sometimes the values 0.8-0.9, adapt better than 1.

  • VAE: This depends on what checkpoint are you using. Mostly it is recommended to use the ‚Äúvae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned‚Äù Stable Diffusion standard.

  • Clip Skip: It was trained on 2, so use 2.

  • Steps and CFG: It is recommended to use Steps from ‚Äú20-40‚Äù and CFG scale from ‚Äú6-8‚Äù, the ideal is: steps 30, CFG 7. For next models, those values could change.

  • Sampler: I use mostly ‚ÄúEulerA‚Äù, ‚ÄúDPM++SDE Karras‚Äù or ‚ÄúDPM++2S a‚Äù. Euler tends to be simpler and more creative. Make experimentation with other samplers if you like.

  • Batch: In txt2img try to put a value of 4 to generate more than 1 image and watch the generations. If you have a good graphic card, you can use ‚ÄúBatch size‚Äù, this will create at same time 4 images, increasing generation time; but if your computer cannot handle this, change to ‚ÄúBatch count‚Äù that will create 4 images in a row (not a same time), but generation time will be more.

  • Image aspect: Try to use these dimensions: 512x512, 768x512, 512x768, but even you can experiment with different. Don't generate bigger images because the style could be lost, if you want to create a bigger image, use hires.fix in txt2img mode, img2img increase method or Ultimate SD Upscale script extension + ControlNet, or just upscaling with GAN models.

  • Create bigger images: There are 4 different methods to create large images in Stable Diffusion, you can check online how to. For first method ‚Äútxt2img hires.fix‚Äù, I recommend you to use upscale model called ‚Äú4x-UltraSharp‚Äù, downloading here just ‚Äú.pth‚Äù file, and then installing it, putting inside ‚ÄúESRGAN‚Äù file. In hires.fix option put any ‚Äúupscale by‚Äù value, and then with a ‚Äúdenoise strength‚Äù of ‚Äú0.5-0.7‚Äù. For the second method, you have to select first the image generated in txt2img and then putting in img2img mode, increasing dimension at least ‚Äú1,5 times‚Äù with a ‚Äúdenoise strength‚Äù from ‚Äú0.3-0.5‚Äù. For the third method, you can use the same configuration of img2img, but activating ‚Äútile‚Äù mode of ‚ÄúControlNet‚Äù extension and also the script of ‚ÄúUltimate SD Upscale‚Äù, but for that, I recommend you to watch a tutorial here. For the last method, you have to pass the generated image in txt2img to ‚Äúextras‚Äù and then select a GAN model and scale it, you can also use the ‚Äú4x-UltraSharp‚Äù model.

  • Get more control of your creation: Use ‚ÄúControlNet‚Äù extension to generate a more controlled shape of what you want, and even you can test it with sketches. Use ‚ÄúScribble‚Äù or ‚ÄúLineart‚Äù modes. For that, I recommend you to install this extension and then learn to how to use. There are plenty of online videos about it.

  • Copy prompt for image metadata: You can download my example images here and put it inside ‚ÄúPNG info‚Äù tab from Automatic1111

Example Prompting:

Positive prompt:¬†

emauromin style, futuristic armchair, finely detailed, purism, ue 5, a computer rendering, minimalism, octane render, 4k <lora:eddiemauroLora2:0.8>

Negative prompt:¬†

EasyNegative, (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, ((monochrome)), ((grayscale)), cropped, text, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, duplicate, blurry, semi-realistic, out of frame, ugly, deformed

Steps: from 20-40 (For EulerA is enough 20, DPM++SDE Karras or DPM++2S a)

What comes for the future

I‚Äôm already trying to enhance the model. This was trained with 512 image aspect, so I will try with 768 (bigger one), and also other configurations (like changing captions, steps, epochs, etc.). items.name: Halcyon
items.description:
Recommended settings:

800x1000 (before hi-res fix)

DPM++ SDE Karras

Clip Skip 1 or 2

I typically use DPM++ SDE Karras but feel free to use your favorite sampler. Most of the images shown are with NO LORA, NO INPAINTING, AND NO CONTROLNET. I am trying to show how good the model is before using them. Obviously you'll be able to push the quality even higher if you use those.

I have spent months working on this model merge, it's an all-around model useful for creating all types of images and is especially useful for larger resolutions and photorealism. You should easily be able to generate 800x1000 images without much duplication or malformation. You can push higher resolutions with diminishing returns.

I think it's closest comparison would be Deliberate but I believe mine is a little better and more versatile. Of course, your opinion may be different.

Note: If you're trying to reproduce my images, you must enable "Enable quantization in K samplers for sharper and cleaner results. This may change existing seeds. Requires restart to apply."
